Package com.vaadin.polymer.paper.widget

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    PaperButton
    Material Design: Buttons
    PaperCheckbox
    paper-checkbox is a button that can be either checked or unchecked.
    PaperDialog
    <paper-dialog> is a dialog with Material Design styling and optional animations when it is
    opened or closed.
    PaperDialogScrollable
    paper-dialog-scrollable implements a scrolling area used in a Material Design dialog.
    PaperDrawerPanel
    paper-drawer-panel contains a drawer panel and a main panel.
    PaperFab
    Material Design: Button
    PaperHeaderPanel
    paper-header-panel contains a header section and a content panel section.
    PaperIconButton
    Material Design: Buttons
    PaperIconItem
    <paper-icon-item> is a convenience element to make an item with icon.
    PaperInput
    <paper-input> is a single-line text field with Material Design styling.
    PaperInputCharCounter
    <paper-input-char-counter> is a character counter for use with <paper-input-container>.
    PaperInputContainer
    <paper-input-container> is a container for a <label>, an <input is="iron-input"> or
    <iron-autogrow-textarea> and optional add-on elements such as an error message or character
    counter, used to implement Material Design text fields.
    PaperInputError
    <paper-input-error> is an error message for use with <paper-input-container>.
    PaperItem
    <paper-item> is a non-interactive list item.
    PaperItemBody
    Use <paper-item-body> in a <paper-item> or <paper-icon-item> to make two- or
    three- line items.
    PaperMaterial
    paper-material is a container that renders two shadows on top of each other to
    create the effect of a lifted piece of paper.
    PaperMenu
    <paper-menu> implements an accessible menu control with Material Design styling.
    PaperProgress
    The progress bars are for situations where the percentage completed can be
    determined.
    PaperRadioButton
    paper-radio-button is a button that can be either checked or unchecked.
    User can tap the radio button to check it.
    PaperRadioGroup
    paper-radio-group allows user to select only one radio button from a set.
    Checking one radio button that belongs to a radio group unchecks any
    previously checked radio button within the same group.
    PaperRipple
    paper-ripple provides a visual effect that other paper elements can
    use to simulate a rippling effect emanating from the point of contact.
    PaperScrollHeaderPanel
    paper-scroll-header-panel contains a header section and a content section.
    PaperSlider
    Fired when the slider’s value changes due to user interaction.
    PaperSpinner
    Element providing material design circular spinner.
    PaperTab
    paper-tab is styled to look like a tab.
    PaperTabs
    paper-tabs makes it easy to explore and switch between different views or functional aspects of
    an app, or to browse categorized data sets.
    PaperTextarea
    <paper-textarea> is a multi-line text field with Material Design styling.
    PaperToast
    paper-toast provides a subtle notification toast.
    PaperToggleButton
    paper-toggle-button provides a ON/OFF switch that user can toggle the state
    by tapping or by dragging the switch.
    PaperToolbar
    paper-toolbar is a horizontal bar containing items that can be used for
    label, navigation, search and actions.
